<br>
Treants bash and kick eh? Wow. So do pets. Guess that evens out eh?<br>
<br>
I agree that the lower level pets will miss more due to level differences, but, that wasn't really the point you were trying to make in your original post. You basically said mage xp sucks because mages suck and you should get used to letting enchanters solo your XP for you. I disagree totally. And, as I stated at the end of my post, them simply gaining a few levels and the 61+ pets (which some of them had if they were equipping pets with belts and Walnan blades) would enable them to do terribly more damage.<br>
<br>
About your level comparison, also flawed. I guess you being a more &quot;experienced&quot; mage would know that the epic mob parses about the same on mobs ranging from level 50 to oh 58 or so. The epic only starts to really show it's age when fighting say golems in Valor or Razorfiends, all lvl 60ish mobs. This group was fighting in PoN however which has friggin green mobs at zone in (to me anyway) which puts them right in the low 50s range, which is right up the epic pets alley, and could even make the earth pets respectable.<br>
<br>
As an aside, actually, it's not funny at all how EoT's proc never gets resisted, since it's a lifetap. And, as a more experienced mage, you'd know about how lifetap is one of the harder spells in the game to resist. Right?<br>
<br>
And I dunno about what kind of mages you play with, but when I play my backstabbing pet o doom, it is TRIVIAL for me to run behind the mob we just pulled, wait 3 seconds for epic (or MT) to gain aggro, and send in pet boom, clean back shots, no muss no fuss. Maybe this situation is foreign to you? Happens to me every day.<br>
<br>
Oh dammit, forgot all about malo/malosin. Mages cast that, helps TONS on making those uber lvl mobs you fight resist the wimpy epic's procs even less. And no offense, but I've killed every mob in PoN and there is not a single lvl 75 mob in that zone. <br>
<br>
Bottom line? You got it.<br>
<br>
A 5 pet group with a chanter can do perfectly well and great in an XP group in PoN. More power to the group that tries to make things WORK, rather than sit and complain about how nobody wants to group with the mage. Tho I rarely have this problem, guess I'm just one helluva personality.<br>
<br>
Oh hey Barf, just so you know, you can replace the chanter with a beastlord, have an all pet party, BST slows are totally acceptable in that sort of group. Let the XP fly my fellow mages!!<br>
